  "protocol_notes": "Complete distal bicep tendon rupture on May 30th; surgery on June 17th; protocol started same night as surgery. All peptide injections administered subcutaneously to stomach/abdomen area. Also on TRT 150mg/week (75mg Sunday and Thursday). Previous experience with BPC/TB for knee pain; local injection to left knee only showed no additional benefit over systemic (stomach) injection to right knee. Cast and sling removed June 25th (8 days post-op). Resumed training (lower body, core, cardio) 2 days post-surgery while in cast/sling. By July 3rd (first PT appointment) was 4-6 weeks ahead of standard recovery timeline. By July 14th (second PT appointment) cleared for barbell squats up to 225lbs and advanced resistance band work.",
